BR_text.BRsummary: Decalarations of type list are not handled correctly in UI (overview and tables)
BR_text.BRdescription:
<denchmark-h:h3>Describe the bug</denchmark-h>
 
 Using the following declaration:
 version: 1
 
 kind: experiment
 
 declarations:
   param1: [0.5, 0.55, 0.6, 0.65, 0.7, 0.75, 0.8, 0.85, 0.9, 0.95]
 
 run:
   cmd: python --param1="{{ param1 }}"
 will result in a parm1 being a list, but the UI does not handle that correctly.
 Same thing for groups:
 version: 1
 
 kind: experiment
 
 hptuning:
   matrix:
     param1:
       values: [[32], [32, 32], [128], [128, 128]]
 
 run:
   cmd: python --param1="{{ param1 }}"
 The cli returns the correct representation:
 <denchmark-link:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1261626/50172724-edb7ce80-02f5-11e9-9fc5-725f96fa859e.png></denchmark-link>
 
 but the UI does a concatenation:
 <denchmark-link:https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1261626/50172781-1344d800-02f6-11e9-9800-3a60f1c8ddde.png></denchmark-link>

comments_0.comment_text: A fix for this ui issue should be part of v0.3.6
